The secondary controller targets mitigation of voltage deviations against the rated values. Following the primary control procedure, the load voltage might not be tuned exactly at the rated value. To overcome the existing fluctuations and regulate the load voltage, the reference bus voltage denoted by subscripts “cv” should be treated as varying with its output current. The following statement is hence considered:5Vcvnew=Vn+RcvIcvnew\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
