Deployment of LBC links is due to lower cost and increased reliability in MGs. In this study, such an application is deemed to maintain the load bus bar voltage at the rated value. In this approach, the updated constant voltage of the reference bus that is determined in (5) is broadcasted to the DERs through LBC links. Figure 3 demonstrates the interconnection of DERs and the communication links. To model the communication time delay in this approach, a suitable transfer function, which has been commonly used in related literature, such as [22, 25, 26], is considered:6Gd=11+τs\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
